The paper focuses on the practical problem of identifying security-relevant commits in open-source software, which is a key concern in software engineering (cs.SE) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves using machine learning to analyze source code repositories, which involves techniques from natural language processing (cs.IR) and document classification (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of source code changes as a key feature for classification, which is relevant to programming languages (cs.PL).
